content:
Inactivate a Messaging Session

When an unresolved conversation has gone idle for a certain period of time, mark it Inactive so that you can accept an incoming messaging session.

This article applies to: Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, enhanced WhatsApp, enhanced Facebook Messenger, enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

To send and receive messages in Messaging for In-App and Web:

Messaging for In-App and Web permission set license
Messaging for In-App and Web user permission

To send and receive messages in enhanced Messaging channels: Messaging Agent

Click the dropdown next to End Chat. Select Customer Inactive.

Inactive sessions are automatically ended after approximately 24 hours. You can also set a time limit for customer inactivity in Messaging for In-App and Web.
